  <compounddef id="compare__mirror_8py" kind="file" language="Python">
    <compoundname>compare_mirror.py</compoundname>
    <innernamespace refid="namespacecompare__mirror">compare_mirror</innernamespace>
    <briefdescription>
<para>Compares C# DES makespan results against the Python mirror DES implementation. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Both implementations share the same architecture — event-driven simulation with per-machine queues and identical dispatching rules with identical tiebreakers — so any delta in their output indicates a real bug in one of the two implementations, not an expected divergence.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Prerequisites</title><para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Run the C# <computeroutput>ValidationExporter</computeroutput> to produce <computeroutput>csharp_makespans.csv</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>csharp_schedules.json</computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Run <computeroutput><ref refid="mirror__des_8py" kindref="compound">mirror_des.py</ref></computeroutput> to produce <computeroutput>mirror_des_makespans.csv</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>mirror_des_schedules.json</computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Run this script from the directory containing all four files: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">python<sp/>compare_mirror.py</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="par"><title>Output</title><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>A per-rule exact-match summary printed to stdout.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>An instance × rule comparison table showing <computeroutput>OK</computeroutput> or a signed integer delta.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>For any mismatches, the first divergent operation (by job/op key) is identified by diffing <computeroutput>csharp_schedules.json</computeroutput> against <computeroutput>mirror_des_schedules.json</computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>mirror_comparison.csv</computeroutput> written to the working directory containing the full merged DataFrame with <computeroutput>match</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>delta</computeroutput> columns.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="par"><title>Exit codes</title><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><computeroutput>0</computeroutput> — all compared pairs matched exactly.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>1</computeroutput> — one or more mismatches found, or required input files were missing. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
</para>
